The best teacher in life is your own experience 

None of us know who we are until we fail. In every lesson there is a hidden blessing.

This past weekend I completed a milestone i set for myself in December and that was completing a HALF marathon (13.1 miles) at @chevronhoustonmarathon 

I not only participated, but I hit a PR — usually I run 13 miles in 2:27 but on THIS DAY I ran a 2:08 🤯

I didn’t know what to expect, but I knew that when I started that I was going to finish without s doubt.

In March I will be doing the FULL marathon (26.2 miles) and I say with confidence that I am READY FOR THAT MF!

I say all this to say that you don’t know what you can accomplish until you put your MIND, BODY & SOUL into whatever it is that you want to.

JUST DONT QUIT 🫶🏾

WE ARE ALPHA 🧡

I have been a coach for 11 years, but it’s what I’ve been through and overcome that has prepared me for where I am today. I’m thankful for my journey, even though it hasn’t been easy. 

I’ve been homeless, slept in my car, walked 3 miles (one way) in the rain and snow just to get to workout because at that time, that’s all I had. I’ve dealt with PTSD from my deployment in 2010, losing people in my life, but what keeps me going is knowing they’re still with me in this chapter of life. 

Fast forward to now, I train all types of people - which is healing for me. I love teaching Alpha and my Alpha community - I can be myself, grow, and continue meeting likeminded people who come together to move their body. 🧡

#LTEmployee #LifeTime #Coach #FindYourPurpose #BetterThanYesterday #Alpha #AlphasUnite #groupfitness #joblove #strength #training

The last couple weeks have been SHIT if I’m being honest, but it don’t matter what obstacles are stacked against you the work MUST be done!

That’s just who I am as a person it may hurt, it may not be fair and that’s OKAY you have to choose whether or not if you’re going to allow that pain to set you back or push you forward 💯 

HYROX SIM RACE @bridgelakescrossfit was amazing 

In the simulation race the runs are 500m vs 1000m which is a huge difference + we ran outside in the Houston heat 🔥 which is a game changer. Thankfully I’ve been training in the heat 🙌🏾 

If you’re looking to get into HYROX or simply interested LET ME KNOW 🫡 the next race will be in Dallas Nov. 18th!

The Turkish Get Up is probably one of my favorite skill movements for numerous reasons from increasing overall strength to stability and mobility. The TGU is great because it recruits every muscle fiber in your body to just complete ☝🏾 rep. It’s probably one of the most technical movements you can do, but also one of the easiest to mess up.

I had my 8:30 Alpha Strength class practice with just their shoe 👟!

You would be surprised how many people messed that up 🙄

#wearealpha #turkishgetup #betterthanyesterday
